  "subject": [],
  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "synopsis",
      "abstract": "House Bill No. 155 provided that State Public Integrity Commission reports be made available to the public on the Commission's website. \r\nHouse Substitute 1 for HB 155 clarified that reports filed with the State Public Integrity Commission, as well as those prepared by it, must be published on the Commission\u2019s website. It also changes the effective date of the Act to January 1 after its enactment into law.\r\nHouse Substitute 2 for HB 155 does all of the same, as well as adds a requirement that public officers annually report in their financial disclosure report to the Public Integrity Commission, which will be published by the Commission, any travel expenses which include transportation, lodging, entertainment, food and beverage, which in aggregate total in excess of $250, paid for by any third party, not including the State. The recipient may rely on representations of value made by the source of the expense payments."
    }
  ],
